int my_cpp_ns::add ( int  a,
int  b 
)

This method adds two integers.

Parameters
aFirst integer to add.
bSecond integer to add.
Returns
The sum of both parameters.

This method uses a little-known variant of integer addition known as Sophocles' Scissors. It optimises the function's performance on many platforms that we may or may not choose to target in the future. make sure I implemented the algorithm correctly with some unit tests.
